Personal Security Dashboard
A web-based security tool built with Python and Flask that analyzes password strength and checks credentials against known data breach databases — privately and securely.
Live demo: (add your link here after deploying)
Built by: Kedar Rohan Nalawade

What It Does

Password Strength Analysis — scores passwords across 6 security criteria including length, character variety, and common password detection
Data Breach Check — queries the HaveIBeenPwned database to check if a password has appeared in any known breach (over 800 million compromised passwords)
Security Recommendations — generates tailored advice based on weaknesses found
Privacy-first design — your password is never transmitted. Uses the k-anonymity model (only a partial SHA-1 hash prefix is sent to the API)


Security Concepts Demonstrated
ConceptImplementationPassword hashingSHA-1 via Python hashlibK-anonymityOnly first 5 chars of hash sent to HaveIBeenPwned APIInput validationServer-side regex checks for character classesEntropy analysisScoring across length, uppercase, lowercase, digits, symbolsThreat intelligenceIntegration with HaveIBeenPwned Pwned Passwords APISecure API designRESTful Flask endpoint, JSON request/response

Tech Stack

Backend: Python 3, Flask
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript
API: HaveIBeenPwned Pwned Passwords (k-anonymity endpoint)
Security: SHA-1 hashing, regex-based entropy analysis


How to Run Locally
1. Clone the repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/yourusername/security-dashboard.git
cd security-dashboard
2. Create and activate a virtual environment
bash# Windows
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

# Mac/Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
3. Install dependencies
bashpip install flask requests
4. Run the app
bashpython app.py
5. Open in your browser
http://127.0.0.1:5000

